---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - Guru Shradha">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6">
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
      </p>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Guru Shradha ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit our website and interact with our Instagram integration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">2.1 Instagram Data</h3>
        <p>
          Our website displays Instagram posts from our official Instagram account. We use the Instagram Graph API to retrieve:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Public Instagram posts from our account</li>
          <li>Post images and videos</li>
          <li>Post captions and metadata</li>
          <li>Post permalinks</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Important:</strong> We do not collect, store, or access any personal Instagram data from visitors to our website. We only display our own public Instagram content.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">2.2 Website Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We may collect standard web analytics information such as:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>IP addresses (anonymized)</li>
          <li>Browser type and version</li>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
          <li>Referring websites</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information solely for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Displaying our Instagram posts on our website</li>
          <li>Improving website performance and user experience</li>
          <li>Understanding how visitors interact with our content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell, rent, or share any personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">4. Instagram Integration</h2>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">4.1 Purpose</h3>
        <p>
          Our Instagram integration serves the sole purpose of displaying our latest Instagram posts on our website to keep visitors updated about our activities, events, and content.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">4.2 Data Access</h3>
        <p>
          We only access data from our own Instagram business account. We do not:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Access other users' Instagram accounts</li>
          <li>Request permissions to user accounts</li>
          <li>Store user Instagram credentials</li>
          <li>Post content to other Instagram accounts</li>
          <li>Access private user information</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-medium">4.3 Token Storage</h3>
        <p>
          We securely store Instagram API access tokens for our own account to maintain the connection between our Instagram account and our website. These tokens are encrypted and stored securely.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement appropriate security measures to protect information against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Secure server infrastructure</li>
          <li>Encrypted data transmission (HTTPS)</li>
          <li>Regular security updates</li>
          <li>Limited access to sensitive data</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use third-party services such as:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Instagram Graph API:</strong> To display our Instagram posts</li>
          <li><strong>Web Analytics:</strong> To understand website usage</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting Services:</strong> To deliver our website content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These services have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to review them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use cookies and similar technologies for:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Essential website functionality</li>
          <li>Analytics and performance monitoring</li>
          <li>Remembering user preferences</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can control cookie settings through your browser preferences.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Know what personal information we collect</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
          <li>Opt-out of data collection where applicable</li>
          <li>Access and correct your personal information</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">11. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> [Your Contact Email]</p>
          <p><strong>Address:</strong> [Your Address]</p>
          <p><strong>Phone:</strong> [Your Phone Number]</p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          Please replace the contact information above with your actual contact details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-4 mt-12 pt-8 border-t">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Meta/Facebook Platform Compliance</h2>
        <p>
          This privacy policy complies with Meta's Platform Policy requirements for apps that access Instagram data. Our app:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Only accesses our own Instagram business account data</li>
          <li>Does not request access to user accounts or personal data</li>
          <li>Uses Instagram data solely for displaying our content on our website</li>
          <li>Maintains appropriate security measures for API access tokens</li>
          <li>Complies with Instagram's Terms of Use and API Terms</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
